WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:22.122 --> 00:25.535
SANTA:
This is Christmastown in the North Pole.

00:25.692 --> 00:28.430
One of the things you need to know
is that everyone who lives here...

00:28.570 --> 00:32.406
is happy all the time. Really happy.

00:32.564 --> 00:35.808
I mean, really, really happy.

00:35.969 --> 00:38.609
Honestly, sometimes it's a bit much.

00:38.772 --> 00:40.979
But happiest of all was Buddy the Elf.

00:42.108 --> 00:46.284
Well, he wasn't really an elf,
but we'll get to that later.

00:46.446 --> 00:50.023
(SINGING) Christmas elves enjoy themselves
By donning gay apparel

00:50.183 --> 00:52.322
Or by singing songs in Santa's shop

00:52.485 --> 00:53.759
Fa-la-la, la-la, la-la-la

00:53.920 --> 00:57.477
Of course, I always like it
When they sing a Christmas carol

00:57.640 --> 01:00.671
I like it even better when they stop

01:01.494 --> 01:05.373
Night and day, they dance and play
They never sleep much either

01:05.532 --> 01:07.307
Would some peace and quiet be a crime?

01:07.467 --> 01:08.810
Fa-la-la-la, la-la-la-la-la

01:08.968 --> 01:12.438
Of course, I love each one of them
But Santa needs a breather

01:12.605 --> 01:15.711
Because they're just so happy
all the time

01:15.875 --> 01:17.548
- They're oddly
- Happy all the time

01:17.710 --> 01:19.781
- Ungodly
- Happy all the time

01:19.946 --> 01:23.519
When they sing until they're bluish
Santa wishes he were Jewish

01:23.683 --> 01:25.219
- 'Cause they're
- Happy all the time

01:25.385 --> 01:27.387
- I swear they're
- Happy all the time

01:27.554 --> 01:31.525
- Bizarrely happy
- All the time

01:31.691 --> 01:35.138
SANTA: But there's an elf called Buddy
Who makes them look apathetic

01:35.295 --> 01:39.004
ALL: If he were any sweeter
We might end up diabetic

01:39.165 --> 01:42.476
SANTA: He's everybody's buddy
But he'll leave your eardrums ringing

01:42.635 --> 01:46.014
ALL: 'Cause everywhere he goes
He has to tell the world he's singing

01:46.172 --> 01:48.675
I'm singing

01:48.842 --> 01:52.221
It's almost Christmas and I'm singing

01:52.378 --> 01:56.224
And I love Santa, so I'm singing

01:56.382 --> 01:58.362
Buddy, you're standing on an elf again.

01:58.518 --> 02:00.395
I thought the floor felt squishy.

02:00.553 --> 02:02.191
Sorry, Ming Ming.

02:02.355 --> 02:03.390
That's okay, Buddy.

02:03.556 --> 02:07.168
(SINGING) My spine will heal
Because I'm happy all the time

02:08.394 --> 02:10.567
Okay, elves, you've got toys to make.

02:10.729 --> 02:12.641
Yay! Time to go to work.

02:12.799 --> 02:14.506
ALL (SINGING): Happy all the time

02:14.667 --> 02:16.078
Happy all the time

02:16.236 --> 02:19.877
Making toys is so appealing
That I spend each morning squealing

02:20.039 --> 02:21.518
True, he's happy all the time

02:21.674 --> 02:24.052
- Who knew? I'm happy all the time
- Happy all the time

02:24.210 --> 02:26.850
He's unnaturally happy

02:27.013 --> 02:32.395
All the time

02:32.552 --> 02:34.691
Happy all the time

02:34.854 --> 02:37.061
(CLATTERING)

02:37.223 --> 02:40.397
Oh, no. I made a big mess again.

02:40.960 --> 02:43.372
It's okay, Buddy.

02:44.097 --> 02:47.670
Why don't you just say it?
I'm a cotton-headed ninny-muggins.

02:47.834 --> 02:49.108
(SOBBING)

02:49.269 --> 02:52.375
(ELVES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

02:52.539 --> 02:54.109
(WIND WHISTLING)

02:56.809 --> 02:59.085
I break everything I touch...

02:59.245 --> 03:00.918
I keep stepping on Ming Ming.

03:01.080 --> 03:04.493
And yesterday,
I only made 400 rocking horses.

03:04.651 --> 03:07.461
Sometimes I don't feel
like I'm an elf at all.

03:07.620 --> 03:08.655
(SIGHS)

03:08.821 --> 03:13.201
Well, Buddy, let me tell you a story
I should have told years ago.

03:13.359 --> 03:14.394
A story.

03:14.561 --> 03:16.563
Whoo-hoo! I love story time.

03:16.729 --> 03:19.676
Holy moly! My legs! My legs!

03:19.832 --> 03:21.812
- Aah!
- A story about your legs?

03:21.968 --> 03:23.311
I love it already.

03:23.469 --> 03:26.279
No, Buddy. Just listen.

03:26.506 --> 03:31.717
Once upon a time, on a Christmas night,
I slid down the chimney of an orphanage.

03:31.878 --> 03:34.620
While I was putting presents
under the tree...

03:34.781 --> 03:38.126
a baby crawled, unseen,
into my toy sack...

03:38.284 --> 03:40.730
and I brought him back here by mistake.

03:40.887 --> 03:45.029
Never having stolen a baby before,
I didn't know what to do.

03:45.191 --> 03:48.536
So the elves took him in
and raised him as one of their own.

03:48.695 --> 03:54.737
And as the years went on,
he grew bigger and bigger and bigger.

03:55.134 --> 03:58.775
Oh. So I'm a giant elf.

03:58.938 --> 04:01.179
- No. Buddy, you're...
- Wait.

04:01.341 --> 04:03.787
I thought this was a story
about your legs.

04:03.943 --> 04:06.617
No, this is your story.

04:06.779 --> 04:08.816
The story of Buddy the Elf.

04:08.982 --> 04:12.555
- Well, actually, Buddy the Human.
- Human?

04:12.719 --> 04:15.359
Your mother's name was Susan Wells.

04:15.521 --> 04:20.527
Now all you have left is your father,
who never knew you were born.

04:20.692 --> 04:22.832
His name is Walter Hobbs...

04:22.996 --> 04:26.739
and he lives in a strange land
called New York City.

04:26.899 --> 04:30.972
And he works right here
in the Empire State Building.

04:31.137 --> 04:32.616
BUDDY: In there? Ha-ha.

04:32.772 --> 04:34.979
Why, he must be teeny-tiny.

04:35.141 --> 04:37.621
Hello, Dad. Dad!

04:37.777 --> 04:41.020
No, don't be scared. I mean you no harm.

04:41.180 --> 04:43.091
This is just a snow globe, Buddy.

04:43.249 --> 04:45.160
Well, of course.

04:45.318 --> 04:48.162
I bet he's the world's greatest dad.

04:48.321 --> 04:49.823
Yeah, about that...

04:49.989 --> 04:51.900
So, what's the world's
greatest dad like?

04:52.058 --> 04:55.164
I mean, does he prefer candy canes
or peppermint sticks?

04:55.328 --> 04:57.569
Uh, he doesn't like either.

04:57.730 --> 05:02.338
Well, the world's greatest dad must have
a top-of-the-line, one-horse open sleigh.

05:03.903 --> 05:06.383
Well, then how does he dash
through the snow?

05:06.539 --> 05:12.182
You see, like a lot of people these days,
he's just lost the Christmas spirit.

05:12.345 --> 05:16.020
But Christmas spirit
is what makes your sleigh fly.

05:16.182 --> 05:20.130
And every year, it's tougher
to get this old girl off the ground.

05:20.286 --> 05:21.492
I guess it could be worse.

05:21.654 --> 05:24.965
- At least he's not on the Naughty List.
- Well...

05:25.124 --> 05:30.005
Can you imagine the world's greatest dad
a Naughty Lister?

05:30.163 --> 05:34.737
I mean, with their beady little eyes
and their naughty little hands...

05:34.901 --> 05:37.541
always grasping for presents
they don't deserve.

05:37.704 --> 05:38.739
Buddy.

05:38.905 --> 05:39.940
(SIGHS)

05:40.006 --> 05:42.052
Let's just cut to the chase.

05:42.208 --> 05:46.179
Your father's been on the Naughty List
for over 50 years.

05:46.346 --> 05:48.485
(GASPS)

05:51.050 --> 05:53.894
Well, this is it. I'm all set to go.

05:54.053 --> 05:57.159
Now, Buddy, are you sure you wanna
go through with this?

05:57.323 --> 05:59.997
New York City can get a little rough.

06:00.159 --> 06:04.198
I've made my mind up, Santa.
I've got to get my dad off the Naughty List.

06:04.364 --> 06:06.844
Well then, good luck, Buddy.

06:06.999 --> 06:09.172
- Farewell, one and all.
- ALL: Bye.

06:09.335 --> 06:12.373
Now, do you remember the way
to New York City?

06:12.538 --> 06:13.642
BUDDY: Sure do.

06:13.806 --> 06:17.185
I go through the Cotton Candy Caverns,
brave the Gumdrop Ocean...

06:17.343 --> 06:20.916
trek through the Candy forest,
then straight on to New York.

06:21.080 --> 06:24.323
- Bye-bye.
- Good luck.

06:27.653 --> 06:29.291
See you later, Buddy.

06:29.455 --> 06:31.264
Good luck finding your dad.

06:31.424 --> 06:33.267
Thanks, Mr. Sea Serpent.

06:34.093 --> 06:36.130
I'm coming, Papa.

06:37.296 --> 06:39.242
(SINGING) We'll make angels in the snow

06:39.399 --> 06:40.969
Till the snow begins to blow

06:41.134 --> 06:43.808
Then we'll run inside
and start a tickle fight

06:45.004 --> 06:48.110
And if it's too cold to sled
We'll eat gingerbread instead

06:48.274 --> 06:51.687
And then cuddle
till he tucks me in at night

06:51.844 --> 06:55.792
And we'll have our pictures taken
For the Christmas cards we're making

06:55.948 --> 06:58.656
Him and me in suits of matching plaid

06:58.818 --> 07:02.493
And when people see us walking
They'll be Google-eyed and gawking

07:02.655 --> 07:08.731
At Buddy and the world's greatest dad

07:09.395 --> 07:13.241
So I'm gonna try my best to be

07:13.399 --> 07:16.505
Everything you'd expect of me

07:16.669 --> 07:23.416
And I promise that I won't stop
until I'm done

07:23.576 --> 07:32.428
So someday you can say
I'm the world's greatest son

07:32.585 --> 07:34.258
Ooh! Sorry.

07:39.158 --> 07:40.967
Wow!

07:41.127 --> 07:42.697
It sure is a big city.

07:42.862 --> 07:45.843
How am I going to find Walter Hobbs?

07:45.998 --> 07:47.739
Walter Hobbs!

07:47.900 --> 07:50.744
Excuse me, have you seen Walter Hobbs?

07:50.903 --> 07:51.973
(COOING)

07:53.473 --> 07:56.352
- Walter?
- My name is Walter.

07:56.509 --> 08:00.184
Dad, it's me, Buddy. I love you so much.

08:00.346 --> 08:03.418
The Hobbs family
is finally back together again.

08:03.583 --> 08:06.393
- My last name is Franklin.
- Oh.

08:06.552 --> 08:08.031
My name is Hobbs.

08:08.187 --> 08:11.566
Then you must be my father.
You're everything I imagined.

08:11.724 --> 08:15.365
I can't believe I found my dad,
Walter Hobbs.

08:15.528 --> 08:17.269
It's Jerry Hobbs.

08:17.530 --> 08:19.840
This is gonna be harder than I thought.

08:19.999 --> 08:21.808
Are you Walter Hobbs?

08:21.968 --> 08:24.710
Are you Walter Hobbs?

08:25.137 --> 08:26.411
(TIRES SCREECHING)

08:26.572 --> 08:27.812
Ooh! Sorry.

08:27.974 --> 08:30.318
Excuse me. Are you Walter Hobbs?

08:30.643 --> 08:32.714
Is that man shouting your name, Walter?

08:32.879 --> 08:35.359
Of course not, Emily.
He's obviously delusional.

08:35.515 --> 08:36.960
Is your name Walter?

08:37.116 --> 08:38.652
(TIRES SCREECHING)

08:39.552 --> 08:42.054
Why is that guy dressed up
like a giant elf?

08:42.221 --> 08:44.929
Christmas always brings out the weirdos.

08:45.091 --> 08:49.562
Son of a nutcracker! My leg feels
like a shattered candy cane.

08:49.729 --> 08:53.108
You know what would be fun?
Let's pick out a Christmas tree tonight.

08:53.266 --> 08:56.736
Brilliant idea. Let's put a dead tree
in the living room.

08:56.903 --> 08:59.577
Come on, Dad.
Where's your Christmas spirit?

08:59.739 --> 09:01.946
He's right. You're turning into a grump.

09:02.108 --> 09:04.918
Besides, we never do anything
as a family anymore.

09:05.344 --> 09:07.756
You know I'm too busy
for all that nonsense.

09:07.914 --> 09:11.225
Hey, why don't you get
your Christmas gift early?

09:11.384 --> 09:13.796
Uh, look, I gotta get back to work.

09:13.953 --> 09:16.229
I'll see you two later.

09:16.889 --> 09:20.029
Michael, you know
your dad's a very busy man.

09:20.192 --> 09:24.197
Hey, I have an idea. Why don't we write Santa
and tell him what we want for Christmas?

09:24.597 --> 09:27.942
I don't believe in Santa.
All I know is what I don't want.

09:29.936 --> 09:31.779
MICHAEL (SINGING): I don't want a check

09:32.071 --> 09:34.278
That's made out to cash

09:34.440 --> 09:38.320
Or a corporate regift
from some secret stash

09:38.477 --> 09:40.150
I'd like a day with my dad

09:40.313 --> 09:42.657
- EMILY: Just a day?
- MICHAEL: Make that two

09:42.815 --> 09:45.352
If you can do that, Santa

09:45.518 --> 09:48.556
I'll believe in you

09:50.423 --> 09:52.630
MICHAEL & EMILY:
Even though it's been years

09:52.792 --> 09:54.863
- Since you heard from me
- Since you heard from me

09:55.027 --> 09:58.497
- I thought it was worth a shot
- I thought it was worth a shot

09:59.198 --> 10:03.340
If it's true that you're magic,
I guarantee

10:03.502 --> 10:06.813
- We could use all the magic you got
- We could use all the magic you got

10:07.540 --> 10:11.249
MICHAEL: I can get you some cookies
If that's what it takes

10:11.410 --> 10:15.324
I've heard stories and I know the deal

10:15.481 --> 10:17.518
- You just slide down the chimney
- You just slide down the chimney

10:17.683 --> 10:19.754
- And fix our mistakes
- And fix our mistakes

10:19.919 --> 10:24.891
- Now, if only I thought you were real
- Now, if only I thought you were real

10:25.057 --> 10:28.129
If you were real

10:29.895 --> 10:33.604
EMILY: I guess that's our list
Our letter is done

10:33.766 --> 10:38.112
Is it really a list
If it adds up to one?

10:38.270 --> 10:40.045
MICHAEL & EMILY:
Make him part of our lives

10:40.206 --> 10:41.981
- Not just passing through
- Not just passing through

10:42.141 --> 10:44.815
- If you can do that, Santa
- If you can do that, Santa

10:44.977 --> 10:48.584
- I'll believe in you
- I'll believe in you

10:49.682 --> 10:53.960
- Yes, if you do that, Santa
- Yes, if you do that, Santa

10:54.120 --> 10:58.262
- I'll believe in you
- I'll believe in you

10:58.424 --> 11:01.234
- So good luck, Santa
- So good luck, Santa

11:01.394 --> 11:05.934
- Here's hoping you come through
- Here's hoping you come through

11:07.033 --> 11:09.946
Signed, Emily

11:10.236 --> 11:16.187
And Michael too

11:21.814 --> 11:23.054
Ooh.

11:26.952 --> 11:28.590
Hot dog.

11:30.489 --> 11:32.400
Mr. Hobbs, you're gonna love this idea.

11:32.558 --> 11:36.563
It's about an outcast reindeer whose glowing
antlers help Santa through a bad storm.

11:36.729 --> 11:40.370
Yeah. We call it
Tony the Lite-Up Antlered Reindeer.

11:40.533 --> 11:41.807
(BOTH SNICKERING)

11:41.967 --> 11:43.844
That sounds awfully familiar.

11:44.870 --> 11:45.940
Uh, then what about this?

11:46.105 --> 11:49.814
It's the story of a grouchy green grouch
who hates Christmas, and then he...

11:49.975 --> 11:52.251
Let me stop you right there,
my brilliant writers.

11:52.411 --> 11:55.017
Greenway Press needs an original story,
and we need it now.

11:55.181 --> 11:56.216
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

11:56.382 --> 11:57.417
- What?
- Mr. Hobbs...

11:57.583 --> 12:00.496
I think someone sent you
a Christmas-gram.

12:00.653 --> 12:01.723
Oh, I love the holidays.

12:01.887 --> 12:03.366
(GASPS)

12:03.522 --> 12:04.660
It's him.

12:04.824 --> 12:08.101
Oh, all right, let's get it over with.
Go ahead.

12:08.260 --> 12:09.432
Get what over with?

12:09.595 --> 12:11.802
Aren't you gonna sing
some dumb song for me?

12:11.964 --> 12:15.673
Sing? Yeah, anything for you.

12:15.835 --> 12:18.577
(SINGING) I'm here with my dad

12:18.738 --> 12:20.445
And we never met

12:20.606 --> 12:22.483
And he wants me to sing him a song

12:22.641 --> 12:26.555
And, um, I love you
I love you, I love you

12:28.447 --> 12:29.687
Huh.

12:30.583 --> 12:31.789
Security.

12:31.951 --> 12:35.296
Oh, hello. Does everyone
in New York hug this tight?

12:35.654 --> 12:36.997
GUARD: Merry Christmas, weirdo.

12:40.392 --> 12:42.065
(MOUSE SQUEAKING)

12:46.265 --> 12:49.439
SANTA: Buddy's first meeting
with his father didn't go so well...

12:49.602 --> 12:51.980
but his luck is about to change.

12:52.138 --> 12:53.310
(BELL RINGING)

12:53.472 --> 12:56.112
(JOVIE HUMMING "JINGLE BELLS")

12:58.711 --> 12:59.746
Huh?

13:00.613 --> 13:01.785
(HEART BEATING RAPIDLY)

13:02.948 --> 13:03.983
(HORNS HONKING)

13:04.150 --> 13:06.562
(CONTINUES HUMMING)

13:06.719 --> 13:08.460
(GASPS THEN TIRES SCREECHING)

13:08.621 --> 13:09.691
BUDDY: Unh!

13:09.855 --> 13:12.165
- Sorry.
- Are you okay?

13:12.324 --> 13:13.564
Oh, yeah. Yeah.

13:13.726 --> 13:16.206
That car wasn't as big
as the last one. Heh-heh.

13:17.863 --> 13:21.504
It's so nice to meet another human
who appreciates elf culture.

13:21.667 --> 13:23.772
Who doesn't love itchy tights, right?

13:23.936 --> 13:26.416
I'm Jovie. You must be the new guy.

13:26.572 --> 13:29.280
First of all, you don't need to try
so hard on the costume.

13:29.441 --> 13:31.284
I sewed it myself.

13:31.443 --> 13:33.980
Uh, cool. Also,
they'll want you to sing...

13:34.146 --> 13:36.820
but no one checks in on you,
so you don't have to.

13:36.982 --> 13:39.360
But singing's the greatest.
Santa always says:

13:39.518 --> 13:43.261
"The best way to spread Christmas cheer
is singing loud for all to hear."

13:43.422 --> 13:46.266
Deck the halls with... Come on.
Boughs of holly

13:46.425 --> 13:48.063
Where's your Christmas spirit?

13:48.227 --> 13:50.639
Nope. Sorry. I don't sing.

13:50.796 --> 13:56.041
You should. I bet your voice is prettier
than the call of an Arctic Warbler seal.

13:56.202 --> 13:57.806
- JOVIE: Oh. Um...
- Ooh, ooh.

13:57.970 --> 14:00.883
It's Santa Claus. I know him.
Do you wanna meet him?

14:01.040 --> 14:02.815
- JOVIE: Uh...
- Come on.

14:02.975 --> 14:05.353
- JOVIE: Aah!
- MAN: Here you go.

14:05.511 --> 14:07.422
Santa. Santa.

14:07.580 --> 14:10.390
- You mind? I'm on a break.
- But it's me.

14:10.549 --> 14:13.894
Santa Claus, Santa Claus. Hi.

14:14.453 --> 14:15.727
Ah, great.

14:16.288 --> 14:18.029
Well, hello there.

14:18.190 --> 14:19.863
Ho, ho, ho.

14:20.025 --> 14:22.505
Wait a second.
His stomach didn't shake...

14:22.661 --> 14:25.403
- Oh, boy.
- ...like a bowl full of jelly. Who are you?

14:25.564 --> 14:28.238
What are you talking about?
I'm Santa Claus.

14:28.400 --> 14:30.744
No, you're not.

14:30.903 --> 14:33.543
- You're a fake.
- I'm fake? Ha-ha.

14:33.706 --> 14:35.982
Hey, buddy, how'd you like
to be dead, huh?

14:36.141 --> 14:40.351
I don't know how you know my name,
but you're not really Santa.

14:40.512 --> 14:42.219
- Look, everybody.
- Aah!

14:45.217 --> 14:47.094
- Fake.
- Argh!

14:47.253 --> 14:51.326
Everybody, listen. He's a fake.
Fake, fake, fake. This guy's a fake.

14:51.490 --> 14:53.265
Fake-o.

14:55.261 --> 14:56.763
This guy's a fake.

14:57.096 --> 14:58.200
Fake Santa.

14:58.364 --> 15:00.537
Fake, fake, fake.

15:01.500 --> 15:02.604
(GROANS)

15:04.370 --> 15:05.678
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

15:05.838 --> 15:07.317
(GASPS)

15:07.840 --> 15:08.875
Fake.

15:09.041 --> 15:11.214
Come on, Buddy, the cops are coming.

15:13.178 --> 15:15.715
Are they like the guys
who hug you out of the building?

15:15.881 --> 15:17.622
What? Just go.

15:17.783 --> 15:19.057
When can I see you again?

15:19.485 --> 15:23.661
Uh, after work, I hang out at the ice rink
at Rockefeller Center.

15:23.822 --> 15:26.234
Uh-huh. I have no idea where that is.

15:26.392 --> 15:29.305
Just look for the giant
Christmas tree. Go.

15:29.461 --> 15:30.906
I love Christmas trees.

15:31.063 --> 15:32.736
(TIRES SCREECHING AND BUDDY SCREAMS)

15:34.400 --> 15:38.246
(MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

15:38.404 --> 15:41.942
BUDDY: Oh. Uh-huh. Stocks and bonds.
Five percent interest...

15:43.008 --> 15:44.988
(GIRLS SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
THEN BUDDY GASPS)

15:45.144 --> 15:47.852
BUDDY: Becky said what? Oh, my gosh.

15:51.150 --> 15:53.391
(DOGS YAPPING)

15:53.585 --> 15:55.656
(BUDDY BARKING)

15:57.289 --> 15:58.324
(PANTING)

15:58.490 --> 15:59.901
- What?
- Oh, uh...

16:00.059 --> 16:02.300
I didn't see you there, Dad. I love you.

16:02.461 --> 16:04.338
Would you stop with that dad stuff?

16:04.596 --> 16:05.870
What do you want?

16:06.231 --> 16:09.269
There's no easy way to say this.

16:09.435 --> 16:11.745
You are on the Naughty List.

16:13.472 --> 16:15.042
(NAUGHTY LISTERS WHISPERING)

16:15.207 --> 16:19.121
Look, I don't believe in Santa Claus
and I don't believe you're my son.

16:19.278 --> 16:21.781
Now, leave me alone! You got that?

16:22.514 --> 16:25.085
But Susan Wells was my mother.

16:25.250 --> 16:27.924
Susan Wells?

16:29.388 --> 16:32.267
Wha...? Uh, you have
another son, Walter?

16:32.424 --> 16:34.768
He may or may not be my son.

16:36.128 --> 16:39.541
Unfortunately,
the facts are pointing towards "may."

16:39.698 --> 16:43.077
Then, until we get this sorted out,
he needs to stay with us.

16:43.235 --> 16:44.407
Yay!

16:44.570 --> 16:47.050
But he thinks he's an elf.

16:47.206 --> 16:49.379
No, I was just raised by them.

16:50.909 --> 16:54.015
It's almost Christmas
and there's no decorations in this house.

16:54.179 --> 16:56.284
Oh, do you wanna decorate the apartment?

16:56.448 --> 16:58.826
WALTER: No way. No decorations.

16:58.984 --> 17:01.624
All that Christmas-spirit stuff
is a scam.

17:01.887 --> 17:06.961
Dad says, "The holidays are a time for us
to make money, not spend it."

17:07.126 --> 17:09.127
No wonder he's on the Naughty List.

17:09.294 --> 17:10.637
Yes, that's right, Michael.

17:10.796 --> 17:14.903
And if I don't come up with a new book idea,
I'm not gonna be making any money.

17:15.233 --> 17:19.478
Come on, Dad. For once, can you
please let us put up some decorations?

17:19.637 --> 17:22.743
- Yeah, please. Please, please, please.
- Please, please, please.

17:22.907 --> 17:25.319
Fine. Just don't go overboard.

17:25.477 --> 17:28.583
- Oh, thank you! Yes!
- Yes! All right!

17:30.649 --> 17:32.720
(SINGING)
There's a saying we have up north

17:32.885 --> 17:35.126
That helps us put our best foot forth

17:35.287 --> 17:37.767
If you wanna deck the halls for Mr. C

17:37.923 --> 17:42.235
Make sure
they're sparkle-jolly-twinkle-jingley

17:42.394 --> 17:44.203
What's that supposed to mean?

17:44.563 --> 17:48.841
When a room is gloomy
And its atmosphere has called it quits

17:49.001 --> 17:53.609
Then you must remember
That December is a time for glitz

17:53.772 --> 17:57.219
Never stop until each limb
On your Christmas tree

17:57.376 --> 18:01.290
Is sparkle-jolly-twinkle-jingley

18:02.381 --> 18:06.625
Pick up every ornament
That's sitting, waiting on a shelf

18:06.785 --> 18:11.029
While you're busy decorating
Why not decorate yourself?

18:11.190 --> 18:14.535
Soon you'll bring a smile
To every person you see

18:15.094 --> 18:19.008
- I'm sparkle-twinkle-jolly... What?
- Close enough.

18:19.164 --> 18:21.405
(SINGING) And if you're at a loss

18:21.567 --> 18:26.641
Remember the phrase that says
To thine own elf be true

18:26.805 --> 18:28.307
To thine own elf be true

18:28.474 --> 18:32.980
For when it comes to Christmas displays

18:33.145 --> 18:35.557
Look inside and you'll know what to do

18:35.714 --> 18:37.990
MICHAEL: You'll know just what to do

18:38.150 --> 18:42.030
ALL: Put some cheery folderol
On every wall and every nook

18:42.187 --> 18:46.533
Tinsel up each corner
Till it's Christmas everywhere you look

18:46.692 --> 18:50.504
Give the world a holiday
That's bright as can be

18:53.499 --> 18:58.312
Make it sparkle-jolly-twinkle-jingle
Shiny-showy-cheery-Kringle

18:58.470 --> 19:00.711
Razzle-dazzle, ring-a-lingle

19:00.873 --> 19:02.910
I can't lie, it makes me tingle

19:03.075 --> 19:08.460
ALL: Sparkle-jolly-twinkle-jingley

19:12.417 --> 19:14.556
- Wow.
- Cool.

19:16.421 --> 19:19.527
SANTA: So Buddy did his best
to spread Christmas cheer.

19:19.691 --> 19:24.970
But it would take more than some tinsel and
lights to get Walter off the Naughty List.

19:25.130 --> 19:26.871
Can you please pass the maple syrup?

19:27.032 --> 19:29.808
I'm sorry. I didn't set out any syrup.

19:29.968 --> 19:31.538
It's spaghetti.

19:31.703 --> 19:34.877
That's okay. I think I have some.

19:35.140 --> 19:37.051
Cool. Hey, me next.

19:37.209 --> 19:39.553
Ugh. I think I'm gonna
stick with coffee.

19:40.546 --> 19:43.049
- BUDDY: I knew it.
- Knew what, Buddy?

19:43.215 --> 19:46.128
I have the world's greatest dad.

19:46.418 --> 19:49.922
Aw, look up, honey. Mistletoe.

19:51.123 --> 19:52.431
Oh.

19:53.158 --> 19:56.970
We've been tinkering with the story
of a snowman that comes to life...

19:57.129 --> 19:59.200
named Freezy the Snowman.

19:59.364 --> 20:01.139
Yeah, yeah, yeah. We even have a song.

20:01.300 --> 20:02.506
(SINGING) Freezy the Snowman

20:02.668 --> 20:04.944
He was made from balls
of snow, and then...

20:05.103 --> 20:06.514
Okay, okay. I've heard enough.

20:06.672 --> 20:07.707
(KAZOO HONKING)

20:07.973 --> 20:11.318
Psst. Dad, Dad,
do you wanna hear me play the kazoo?

20:13.011 --> 20:15.013
Buddy, enough with the kazoo!

20:17.249 --> 20:21.197
I'm sorry. But my boss, Mr. Greenway,
gets really cranky when he's upset.

20:21.353 --> 20:22.957
GREENWAY:
What kind of an office is this?

20:23.121 --> 20:25.226
Doesn't anyone do any work around here?

20:25.390 --> 20:27.996
- I ought to fire the whole lot of you.
- Shh.

20:28.160 --> 20:31.505
GREENWAY: I've never seen an office
as poorly run as this one.

20:31.663 --> 20:35.178
- WORKER 1: Good morning, Mr. Greenway.
- WORKER 2: Good morning, Mr. Greenway.

20:35.334 --> 20:37.143
Zip it. You're fired!

20:37.302 --> 20:40.181
- Buy some cookies?
- You're fired!

20:41.540 --> 20:42.644
You're fired!

20:43.141 --> 20:45.519
Fired! Fired! Fired!

20:45.677 --> 20:47.281
Fired!

20:47.546 --> 20:51.460
What am I paying you for?
Get back to work!

20:51.650 --> 20:55.860
Oh. When my boss is having a tough day,
we bring him milk and cookies...

20:56.021 --> 20:58.592
and sing Christmas carols
so he forgets his troubles.

20:58.757 --> 21:00.896
Buddy, you're a genius.

21:01.159 --> 21:05.107
We distract Greenway with tinsel and eggnog,
and all that other holiday nonsense...

21:05.264 --> 21:07.437
make him feel that Christmas spirit...

21:07.599 --> 21:10.136
and he won't notice
how lame our ideas are.

21:10.902 --> 21:15.749
Oh. I can help decorate. And we can all
dress up like gingerbread men and sing.

21:15.907 --> 21:18.615
Uh, that's okay, Buddy.
We can handle it from here.

21:18.777 --> 21:20.779
Why don't you take
the rest of the day off?

21:20.946 --> 21:22.755
Thanks, Pop. You're the greatest.

21:22.914 --> 21:25.190
(KAZOO HONKING)

21:25.350 --> 21:28.695
Uh, where's Rockefeller Center?

21:32.791 --> 21:34.828
- BUDDY: Hey, Jovie!
- Huh?

21:38.397 --> 21:42.004
You weren't kidding. That is a big tree.

21:42.167 --> 21:45.410
Yeah, my mom used to take me here
over the holidays as a kid.

21:45.570 --> 21:48.915
It's kind of fun watching skaters
fall on their butts.

21:49.074 --> 21:50.451
(BOTH LAUGHING)

21:50.609 --> 21:52.850
- Let's go skating.
- Mm...

21:53.545 --> 21:54.785
I'm not very good.

21:54.946 --> 21:58.086
Well, neither am I.
I was the worst skater in the North Pole.

21:58.250 --> 21:59.957
They called me the triple klutz.

22:00.118 --> 22:02.120
Now, please, don't laugh.

22:02.287 --> 22:04.767
Okay. Do you need to hold onto me?

22:04.923 --> 22:06.163
Huh?

22:24.209 --> 22:27.884
- Uh, oh, yeah, Buddy. You're terrible.
- I know.

22:28.046 --> 22:31.892
The final rotation of my octuple salchow
wasn't very clean. Oh.

22:32.050 --> 22:33.927
Anyway, so who's your favorite reindeer?

22:34.086 --> 22:37.295
Mine's Dasher, followed by Comet,
but he can be a little messy.

22:37.456 --> 22:40.596
I wish I could still get as excited
about the holidays as you.

22:40.759 --> 22:43.865
I always say the best way
to spread Christmas cheer...

22:44.029 --> 22:46.566
is singing loud for all to hear.

22:46.732 --> 22:48.905
I don't sing, remember?

22:49.067 --> 22:52.947
(SINGING)
Come on, Jovie, singing can be easy

22:53.105 --> 22:54.140
Please, stop.

22:54.306 --> 22:57.310
It's fun, it's free,
and best of all it's...

22:57.476 --> 22:59.820
- Totally cheesy?
- Come on.

22:59.978 --> 23:04.620
(SINGING) All you have to do
Is move your voice much higher

23:04.783 --> 23:07.821
High, low, high, low

23:07.986 --> 23:09.021
High

23:09.187 --> 23:12.794
It's just like talking only you sustain it
And make it sound pretty

23:13.859 --> 23:14.894
No.

23:15.060 --> 23:18.803
Just sing a Christmas song

23:18.964 --> 23:22.810
It's like magic if things go wrong

23:22.968 --> 23:26.541
Just spread some Christmas cheer

23:26.705 --> 23:32.053
By singing loud for all to hear

23:32.210 --> 23:35.123
- But when I sing, people stare.
- That's the point.

23:35.280 --> 23:39.626
(SINGING) And if you're short on cheer
Think about that year

23:39.785 --> 23:43.961
You woke up to find
A brand-new snow had fallen

23:44.122 --> 23:48.628
The ornaments you made
Way back in second grade

23:48.794 --> 23:52.799
Untangling the Christmas lights
Took your father several nights

23:52.964 --> 23:57.071
Your mother claimed that she had proof
There were reindeer on the roof

23:57.235 --> 24:02.514
Remember who you were back then
Let those moments live again

24:02.674 --> 24:05.450
Come on, Jovie. Try it for me.

24:05.610 --> 24:08.819
(SINGING) Just sing a Christmas song

24:08.980 --> 24:10.015
That's it.

24:10.182 --> 24:12.924
It's like magic if things go wrong

24:13.084 --> 24:14.154
Keep going.

24:14.319 --> 24:17.732
Think of the joy you'll bring

24:17.889 --> 24:21.928
- If you just close your eyes
- If you just close your eyes

24:22.093 --> 24:25.802
- If you just close your eyes
- If you just close your eyes

24:25.964 --> 24:29.070
- If you just close your eyes
- If you just close your eyes

24:29.234 --> 24:34.707
- And sing
- And sing

24:42.380 --> 24:44.360
Aw, shucks.

24:46.218 --> 24:49.859
- CHADWICK: And so...
- Freezy, the green grouchy snowman...

24:50.021 --> 24:52.968
with the light-up antlers
flew through the terrible storm...

24:53.124 --> 24:56.401
and delivered the presents
to the Whys of Whyville.

24:56.561 --> 24:59.007
Merry Christmas, everyone.

24:59.164 --> 25:01.346
You know, maybe it's the eggnog talking,

25:01.496 --> 25:04.429
but this is the best idea
I've heard all year.

25:04.579 --> 25:07.583
Thank you, Mr. Greenway.
We put a lot of work into it.

25:07.739 --> 25:09.912
Dad, Dad, Dad.

25:10.075 --> 25:12.885
I'm in love! I'm in love! Love!

25:13.044 --> 25:15.524
(SINGING) Just sing a Christmas song...

25:15.680 --> 25:16.715
(BUDDY GASPS)

25:17.048 --> 25:19.961
You didn't tell me
you had elves working here.

25:20.118 --> 25:23.190
Is, uh, this part of the presentation?
Heh-heh.

25:23.355 --> 25:24.390
Very funny.

25:24.556 --> 25:25.660
No, this is...

25:25.824 --> 25:28.828
Oh, no. Did you leave your uniform
at Santa's workshop?

25:28.994 --> 25:30.974
That's okay, I have a spare.

25:31.129 --> 25:34.338
If this is supposed to be putting me
in the Christmas spirit...

25:34.499 --> 25:36.103
it's not working.

25:36.268 --> 25:39.806
Okay, arm through here.
Stop squirming, stop squirming.

25:39.971 --> 25:41.917
Ouch. You got me in the eye. Ha-ha.

25:42.674 --> 25:44.244
These are too big.

25:44.409 --> 25:48.050
You must have the smallest feet
in the whole North Pole.

25:48.213 --> 25:51.456
Tiny feet.
Look at your little tiny fee...

25:52.717 --> 25:57.097
Aah! I have never been so humiliated
in my life, Hobbs!

25:57.255 --> 26:00.793
And I can't believe I almost fell
for your song and dance!

26:00.959 --> 26:02.597
Your story was terrible!

26:02.761 --> 26:05.367
Sir, have a little more eggnog? Please?

26:05.530 --> 26:09.478
Tomorrow night,
you'd better bring me an original idea!

26:09.634 --> 26:12.012
Tomorrow night?
But that's Christmas Eve.

26:12.170 --> 26:15.982
I don't care! You're gonna give me
the best Christmas story ever...

26:16.141 --> 26:17.449
or you're fired!

26:17.609 --> 26:19.384
- But...
- Fired!

26:19.544 --> 26:23.583
Get out of my way, you pencil-necks!

26:23.748 --> 26:24.783
BUDDY: Wow.

26:25.116 --> 26:28.290
- He's an angry elf.
- Buddy!

26:28.453 --> 26:30.763
- Do you realize what you've just done?
- No.

26:30.922 --> 26:32.458
Get out!

26:32.624 --> 26:36.504
- Out where?
- I don't care. I don't care! Just go!

26:36.661 --> 26:39.141
You're not an elf! You're not my son!

26:53.311 --> 26:54.551
SANTA: It was Christmas Eve...

26:54.713 --> 26:58.820
and Buddy had never been more unhappy
in his entire life.

26:58.984 --> 27:02.454
Because of those terrible things
Walter said to him...

27:02.621 --> 27:07.570
he left their home and wandered alone
through the streets of the city.

27:07.726 --> 27:09.831
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

27:24.376 --> 27:25.855
Give me another.

27:26.011 --> 27:28.048
I think you've had enough, buddy.

27:28.213 --> 27:30.159
I'll tell you when I've had enough.

27:30.315 --> 27:33.194
Just keep the syrup coming.

27:37.389 --> 27:38.663
(SIGHS)

27:38.857 --> 27:43.363
How can a city so big
have so little Christmas spirit?

27:43.528 --> 27:45.405
It's getting worse and worse every year.

27:45.563 --> 27:49.170
At least you're an elf. You don't have
to listen to kids telling you you're a fake.

27:49.334 --> 27:51.007
Well, you are fake.

27:51.169 --> 27:52.807
You're all fakes.

27:52.971 --> 27:54.814
Fakes.

27:54.973 --> 27:57.146
We're just trying to spread
a little Christmas cheer.

27:57.308 --> 27:58.912
And what do we get in return?

27:59.077 --> 28:02.058
Bruises on our thighs
in the shape of kids' butts.

28:02.213 --> 28:04.659
Years ago, kids would light up
when they saw you.

28:04.816 --> 28:07.387
Now they just sit on your lap
and text each other.

28:07.552 --> 28:09.964
No respect at all.

28:11.423 --> 28:12.458
(SIGHS)

28:12.624 --> 28:15.104
(SINGING) Used to be

28:15.260 --> 28:18.673
I'd stand on the busiest corner

28:18.863 --> 28:25.439
Ring my bell
And make the people smile

28:25.603 --> 28:31.781
Nowadays, they pass me by
And who knows why?

28:31.943 --> 28:38.258
Could it be that old St. Nick's
Gone out of style?

28:38.416 --> 28:41.954
Well, nobody cares
Nobody cares

28:42.120 --> 28:44.726
Nobody cares about Santa

28:45.457 --> 28:48.199
They read their list
Then you get dismissed

28:48.359 --> 28:52.273
'Cause nobody cares about Santa Claus

28:52.430 --> 28:55.775
Is this all a sign?

28:55.934 --> 28:58.938
Is this all an awful sign?

28:59.104 --> 29:02.449
Of a sad decline?

29:02.607 --> 29:05.213
A miserable, sad decline

29:05.376 --> 29:08.255
I never knew such disrespect

29:08.413 --> 29:11.622
Could ever have existed

29:11.783 --> 29:18.723
No wonder this whole city
Has been naughty-listed

29:18.890 --> 29:22.895
I kind of get that feeling too

29:23.061 --> 29:25.564
Well, nobody cares

29:25.730 --> 29:28.006
Nobody cares

29:28.166 --> 29:31.045
Nobody cares about Santa

29:31.870 --> 29:33.372
The bringer of bliss

29:33.538 --> 29:37.884
What kind of world is this?

29:38.042 --> 29:41.615
Where nobody cares about weary

29:41.780 --> 29:43.225
Fed up

29:43.381 --> 29:45.691
Ready-to-hang-the-sled-up

29:45.850 --> 29:50.026
Santa Claus?

29:50.188 --> 29:51.565
Ho, ho, ho?

29:51.723 --> 29:53.225
No, no, no

29:53.591 --> 29:54.968
(ALL SCREAMING)

29:55.126 --> 29:56.571
(BUDDY GROANS)

30:00.832 --> 30:03.335
- EMILY: Buddy, we're home.
- MICHAEL: Buddy.

30:03.501 --> 30:04.741
EMILY: Where is he?

30:07.205 --> 30:09.344
We have to find him, Mom.

30:10.842 --> 30:14.551
WALTER: Okay, Mr. Greenway, we've come up
with a couple quite original ideas.

30:14.712 --> 30:16.555
- Dad. We need your help.
- Wha...?

30:16.714 --> 30:18.785
Michael, Emily, what are you doing here?

30:18.950 --> 30:22.022
- I told you I have to work tonight.
- Buddy ran away, Walter.

30:22.187 --> 30:24.360
What's going on here, Hobbs?

30:24.522 --> 30:26.695
Sorry, Mr. Greenway.
It'll just be a second.

30:26.858 --> 30:29.862
Please. This is a very
important meeting.

30:30.028 --> 30:32.269
What's more important than your family?

30:32.430 --> 30:36.572
I'll tell you, snotnose.
Money is what's more important.

30:36.835 --> 30:39.281
Please, don't speak to my son that way,
Mr. Greenway.

30:39.437 --> 30:43.647
Well, someone has to,
or else he'll turn out like your other kid.

30:43.808 --> 30:47.221
I hope I turn out like him.
Buddy cares about everybody.

30:47.512 --> 30:49.423
You just care about yourself.

30:51.049 --> 30:53.256
Come on, Mom. Dad needs to work.

30:53.418 --> 30:56.592
Yes, thank you.
You've wasted enough of our time.

30:56.754 --> 30:58.927
Now, go ahead, Hobbs.

30:59.324 --> 31:01.770
Uh, yeah.

31:02.160 --> 31:05.835
Emily? Michael? Wait.
You'll wanna hear this too.

31:06.231 --> 31:07.938
Here's the story.

31:08.099 --> 31:09.169
It's called:

31:09.701 --> 31:11.738
I Quit.

31:13.104 --> 31:14.515
Excuse me?

31:14.672 --> 31:17.243
That's right, Greenway. I quit.

31:17.408 --> 31:20.617
You wanna spend Christmas
on the unemployment line?

31:20.778 --> 31:23.850
No, I wanna spend Christmas
with my family.

31:24.015 --> 31:26.495
Singing, drinking eggnog,
and opening presents.

31:26.651 --> 31:27.789
All right, Dad.

31:27.952 --> 31:30.432
Oh, Walter, it's about time.

31:30.588 --> 31:32.693
Let's go find your brother.

31:34.058 --> 31:36.561
(GROWLING)

31:41.566 --> 31:44.979
Oh, look, another fake Santa.

31:45.136 --> 31:48.015
You're not fooling anyone
with your flying sleigh.

31:48.172 --> 31:53.178
I can see the strings.
You're a big fat fakety-fake fake.

31:53.578 --> 31:54.955
(SLEIGH SPUTTERING)

31:55.113 --> 31:57.650
Whoa. That's the real Santa.

31:57.815 --> 32:00.193
His sleigh doesn't have enough
Christmas spirit.

32:00.351 --> 32:01.625
He's gonna crash.

32:01.786 --> 32:04.164
I'm coming, Santa.

32:04.322 --> 32:05.357
(CRASH)

32:05.523 --> 32:06.695
Sorry.

32:06.858 --> 32:09.202
(SLEIGH SPUTTERING)

32:09.861 --> 32:12.341
Buddy? Buddy?

32:12.497 --> 32:13.737
Where could he have gone?

32:13.898 --> 32:17.004
We really need a Christmas miracle
right now.

32:19.837 --> 32:22.340
Did you see what I just saw?

32:22.507 --> 32:23.952
(SINGING) I saw a tiny sleigh

32:24.108 --> 32:28.682
Make its tiny way
Right across the sky

32:28.846 --> 32:31.850
There wasn't time to think
There wasn't time to blink

32:32.016 --> 32:34.792
Before it zoomed right by

32:34.953 --> 32:36.626
And everything I knew, I knew

32:36.788 --> 32:41.259
And everything that you knew too
Is absolutely now untrue because

32:41.426 --> 32:45.670
Without a doubt there is a Santa Claus

32:45.830 --> 32:47.434
I didn't see Santa Claus, Michael.

32:47.598 --> 32:50.511
EMILY (SINGING): It's hard to be sedate
Or keep your head on straight

32:50.668 --> 32:54.115
When fairy tales come true

32:54.272 --> 32:56.809
Though I can't complain
'Cause if I'm insane

32:56.975 --> 33:00.388
That means you are too

33:00.545 --> 33:03.116
So why don't we make a pact
